    <h1>Indian Government Health Guidelines & Financial Support Programs</h1>
    
    <div class="guidelines-grid">
      <!-- Box 1 -->
      <div class="guideline-box">
        <div class="guideline-header">
          Health Insurance Schemes
          <button class="show-button" onclick="toggleContent(this)">Show More</button>
        </div>
        <div class="guideline-content">
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>1. Ayushman Bharat Pradhan Mantri Jan Arogya Yojana (AB PM-JAY)</h4>
            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/R.e05620409d416f188ce8dae033bd2f48?rik=VSEsLRR90HreEg&riu=http%3a%2f%2fppid.qcin.org%2fpublic%2fuploads%2fcasestudyimages%2f1574057544.5.jpg&ehk=ihhiJ%2bkEts49tKyBJHzXGRA7GL0HbmOz%2byWlqRVLrm4%3d&risl=&pid=ImgRaw&r=0">
        </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Coverage:</strong> Health insurance coverage of ₹5 lakh per family per year for secondary and tertiary care hospitalization.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Poor and vulnerable families identified based on SECC database; approximately 10.74 crore families (50 crore people).
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> Covers 3 days of pre-hospitalization and 15 days of post-hospitalization expenses, 1,400+ procedures, all pre-existing conditions.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> PMJAY Golden Card can be obtained at PM-JAY empaneled hospitals or Common Service Centers with Aadhaar card, ration card, or other specified ID.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://beneficiary.nha.gov.in/">https://beneficiary.nha.gov.in/</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>2. Central Government Health Scheme (CGHS)</h4>
            <img src="https://healthnewsreporting.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/12/Key-Functions-of-the-Central-Government-Health-Scheme-CGHS-Bangalore.jpg">
        </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Coverage:</strong> Comprehensive medical care to central government employees, pensioners, and their dependents.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> All central government employees, pensioners, members of Parliament, ex-MPs, freedom fighters, and their dependent family members.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> OPD consultation, medicines, lab tests, imaging, hospitalization, specialized treatments at empaneled private hospitals.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Submit application through parent department with prescribed forms, ID proof, and photos.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://cghs.gov.in/CghsGovIn/faces/ViewPage.xhtml">https://cghs.gov.in/CghsGovIn/faces/ViewPage.xhtml</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>3. Employees' State Insurance Scheme (ESIS)</h4>
            <img src="https://4.bp.blogspot.com/-4Wi0qdBDez0/WXmhYt1ar6I/AAAAAAAABWE/cgU4XIo_uKAqrCAZN2fxhL_fq31j548jACEwYBhgL/s1600/13.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Coverage:</strong> Self-financing health insurance and social security scheme for Indian workers.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Employees earning up to ₹21,000 per month in organizations with 10+ employees (20+ in some states).
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> Medical, sickness, maternity, disability, and dependent benefits; super-specialty treatment.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Employer registers employees; employee contribution is 0.75% of wages, employer contributes 3.25%.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://www.esic.gov.in/">https://www.esic.gov.in/</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>4. Rashtriya Swasthya Bima Yojana (RSBY)</h4>
            <img src="https://th.bing.com/th/id/OIP.hlBHQJoIFnbCvJM0RXhVBwAAAA?rs=1&pid=ImgDetMain">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Coverage:</strong> Health insurance coverage up to ₹30,000 for BPL families (now largely merged with PM-JAY).
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> BPL families, MGNREGA workers, domestic workers, sanitation workers, rickshaw pullers, rag pickers.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> Cashless hospitalization in public and private hospitals, maternity benefits, transport allowance.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Biometric smart card issued through enrollment camps in villages/urban areas.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://www.india.gov.in/spotlight/rashtriya-swasthya-bima-yojana">https://www.india.gov.in/spotlight/rashtriya-swasthya-bima-yojana</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>5. Pradhan Mantri Suraksha Bima Yojana (PMSBY)</h4>
            <img src="https://www.loanamount.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/02/Pradhan-Mantri-Suraksha-Bima-Yojana-PMSBY.png">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Coverage:</strong> Accident insurance with coverage of ₹2 lakh for accidental death or disability.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Indian citizens aged 18-70 years with a bank account.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> ₹2 lakh for accidental death/permanent disability, ₹1 lakh for partial disability.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Annual premium of ₹12 auto-debited from bank account; apply through bank or online.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://financialservices.gov.in/beta/en/pmsby">https://financialservices.gov.in/beta/en/pmsby</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <h4>6. State Government Health Insurance Schemes</h4>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Examples:</strong> Tamil Nadu's Chief Minister's Comprehensive Health Insurance Scheme, Kerala's Karunya Arogya Suraksha Padhathi (KASP), Karnataka's Arogya Bhagya, etc.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Varies by state, typically covering BPL families and specific vulnerable groups.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> Coverage ranges from ₹1.5 lakh to ₹5 lakh depending on the state.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Through state health departments, district hospitals, or specified enrollment centers.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://beneficiary.nha.gov.in/">https://beneficiary.nha.gov.in/</a>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Box 2 -->
      <div class="guideline-box">
        <div class="guideline-header">
          Maternal & Child Health Programs
          <button class="show-button" onclick="toggleContent(this)">Show More</button>
        </div>
        <div class="guideline-content">
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>1. Pradhan Mantri Matru Vandana Yojana (PMMVY)</h4>
            <img src="https://images.ctfassets.net/uwf0n1j71a7j/3of11h5CPNlBXSSsfVKJl4/ccd206609c735d70a7df236bf5113d71/pradhan-mantri-matru-vandana-yojana.png">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefit:</strong> Cash incentive of ₹5,000 in three installments for first living child.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> Pregnant women and lactating mothers, excluding those who receive similar benefits under other schemes.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Process:</strong> First installment (₹1,000) at early registration, second (₹2,000) at 6 months with at least 1 ANC, third (₹2,000) after childbirth registration and first vaccination.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Apply at Anganwadi centers or health facilities with Aadhaar card, bank account, and ID proof.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://pmmvy.wcd.gov.in/">https://pmmvy.wcd.gov.in/</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>2. Janani Suraksha Yojana (JSY)</h4>
            <img src="https://www.impactguru.com/info/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/Janani-Suraksha-Yojana-Scheme-800x600-1.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefit:</strong> Cash assistance for institutional delivery; ₹1,400 in rural and ₹1,000 in urban areas for low-performing states; ₹700 in rural and ₹600 in urban areas for high-performing states.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> All pregnant women in low-performing states; BPL, SC/ST women in high-performing states.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Components:</strong> Free delivery, free C-section, free drugs and consumables, free diagnostics, free diet during stay, free transport.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> Register at nearest health center with ID proof, BPL card (if applicable), and bank account details.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://www.nhm.gov.in/index1.php?lang=1&level=3&sublinkid=841&lid=309">https://www.nhm.gov.in/index1.php?lang=1&level=3&sublinkid=841&lid=309</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>3. Janani Shishu Suraksha Karyakram (JSSK)</h4>
            <img src="https://www.godigit.com/content/dam/godigit/directportal/en/contenthm/janani-shishu-suraksha-yojana.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefit:</strong> Entitles pregnant women to absolutely free delivery including C-section in public health institutions.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> All pregnant women and sick newborns accessing public health institutions.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Services:</strong> Free drugs, consumables, diagnostics, blood, diet, transport to and from facility, exemption from all user charges.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> No formal application; services provided at all government hospitals.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://www.nhm.gov.in/index4.php?lang=1&level=0&linkid=150&lid=171">https://www.nhm.gov.in/index4.php?lang=1&level=0&linkid=150&lid=171</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>4. LaQshya (Labour Room Quality Improvement Initiative)</h4>
            <img src="https://digitallylearn.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LaQshya-its-Significance-UPSC-IAS-316x200.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Objective:</strong> Improve quality of care in labour rooms and maternity operation theatres.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Facilities Covered:</strong> All Medical College Hospitals, District Hospitals, and high case-load CHCs/SDHs.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefits:</strong> Improved infrastructure, training for healthcare providers, standard protocols, respectful maternity care.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Implementation:</strong> Through National Health Mission at identified healthcare facilities.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
                <strong>More Info:</strong><a href="https://nhm.gov.in/index1.php?lang=1&level=3&sublinkid=1307&lid=690">https://nhm.gov.in/index1.php?lang=1&level=3&sublinkid=1307&lid=690</a>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="scheme-card">
            <div class="name">
            <h4>5. Pradhan Mantri Surakshit Matritva Abhiyan (PMSMA)</h4>
            <img src="https://indianews.in/wp-content/uploads/2022/01/Pradhan.jpg">
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Benefit:</strong> Free antenatal check-ups by gynecologists/doctors on the 9th of every month at designated government facilities.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Eligibility:</strong> All pregnant women in 2nd and 3rd trimesters.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Services:</strong> Quality ANC including screening for high-risk pregnancies, early detection of complications, free ultrasound, blood and urine tests.
            </div>
            <div class="scheme-detail">
              <strong>Application:</strong> No formal application; visit designated government health facilities on the 9th of each month.
